如何编写吸引访问者点击的号召性用语https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/31435/how-to-write-call-to-action-copy-that-gets-visitors-clicking.aspx <div class="hs-featured-image-wrapper">; <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/31435/how-to-write-call-to-action -copy-that-gets-visitors-clicking.aspx" title="" class="hs-featured-image-link">; <img src="https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/call%20to% 20happy.jpg" alt="在电子邮件上写号召性用语的人" class="hs-featured-image" style="width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;">; </a>; </div>; <p>;良好的写作在营销中很重要。能够清晰地表达想法对于吸引潜在客户的注意力至关重要。让我们以号召性用语 (CTA) 为例。</p>; <p>;良好的写作对于营销至关重要。能够清晰地表达想法对于吸引潜在客户的注意力至关重要。让我们以号召性用语 (CTA) 为例。</p>; <p class="hs-migerated-cms-post">;</p>; <p>;如果您制作的文案无法吸引访问者，这可能会损害您的点击率、潜在客户转化率和销售量。</p>; <p>;在这篇博文中，我们将讨论一些重要的文案写作经验，您应该将其应用到 CTA 中，以增加流量，产生更多潜在客户，并将用户转化为客户。</p>; <p class="hs-migerated-cms-post">;<a href="#call-to-action">;什么是号召性用语？</a >;<br>;<a href="#how">;如何编写号召性用语</a>;</p>; <p>;<a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot .com/cs/ci/?pg=400cd460-b98f-401b-a565-0dc8cd51719c&amp;pid=53&amp;ecid=&amp;hseid=&amp;hsic=">;<img class="hs-cta-img" style="高度：自动！重要；宽度：自动！重要；最大宽度：100％！重要；边框宽度：0px；/*hs-extra-styles*/；边距：0自动；显示：块；边距顶部： 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="立即下载：28 个免费 CTA 模板" height="60" width="356" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/ 400cd460-b98f-401b-a565-0dc8cd51719c.png"align="middle">;</a>;</p>; <a>;</a>; <h2>;<strong>;什么是号召性用语？ </strong>;</h2>; <p>;<a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing/calls-to-action">;号召性用语 (CTA)</a>;是提示读者采取所需行动的单词或短语。在营销中，CTA 出现在整个营销活动文案中，以说服您的受众通过按钮或超链接进入销售渠道的下一步。</p>; <p>;您的 CTA 可能会提示人们执行以下操作之一：</p>; >; <ul>; <li>;订阅您的电子邮件通讯。</li>; <li>;下载电子书。</li>; <li>;注册一个帐户。</li>; </ul>; <p>;如果您想要说服更多的人采取下一步行动，您的 CTA 必须足够引人注目，让他们点击。这就是为什么了解如何编写 CTA 至关重要。</p>; <a>;</a>; <h2>;<strong>;如何编写号召性用语</strong>;</h2>; <p>;有一个编写有效的号召性用语的特殊技巧——它既是艺术又是科学。对我们来说幸运的是，通过足够的练习可以编写强大的 CTA（或使用 <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing/calls-to-action">;CTA 工具来帮助您入门</a>;）。</p>; <p>;如果您想练习，请按照这些写作技巧来<a href="https://offers.hubspot.com/call-to-action-templates">;制作强大的CTA</a>;，可增加流量并将潜在客户转化为客户。</p>; <p>;<img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/vLOUPx-uipgk7HcayPuAJzpE2-TZfUddNRG-yeDB0UMRm7fGibRws1adUveT4jLpUGAT5RYPCV1j1RxxyVY2JrqtvBagK9FTA_g7cnqw dfF2YOvGYghdpNS8tJqKUPymSv0SNUrkV9hTzliQ1BOe9g4" style="margin-left : 自动; 右边距: 自动; 显示: 块; 宽度: 650px; 高度: 自动; 最大宽度: 100%;" title="" alt="编写号召性用语。包括数字。根据设备定制号召性用语。谨慎使用副词。保持较少的字符数。使语言更少技术性，更实用。发挥创意和使用个性。从强动词开始。">;</p>; <h3>;1.从强有力的动词开始。</h3>; <p>;经典书中的第一条建议<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Writing-Tools-Essential-Strategies-Writer/dp/0316014990" >; <em>;写作工具</em>;</a>;鼓励作者以主语和动词开始句子。在英语中，我们从左到右阅读，动词和主语帮助我们快速收集句子的含义。</p>; <p>;尽管这些事实可能很重要，但在制作在线 CTA 时承认这一点对于吸引读者的注意力至关重要比振翅飞翔的鸟儿的影子更难以捉摸。</p>; <p>;查看下面来自 HubSpot 登陆页面之一的示例。您会注意到每个句子开头的第一个单词是一个面向动作的动词。 “推动”、“开始”和“创造”等词语切中要点并激发行动，立即带来积极的结果。</p>; <p>;<strong>;<img src="https://lh5 .googleusercontent.com/6kz1MldpAaMsmSkPblt3e06jUcBhfCHEWoVI_93bBH61HVNMEbx2zEnaPlMi2h-vTkPqy0cs3guBpG-3xxEWZeMasWjcZI7lMpOHgc4F0w3iIhXbNXnsL1cTZjVsQMghrOfH nvXcY-aj6gw1Rt4XCGc" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" title="" alt="如何编写号召性用语：此 HubSpot 登陆页面上的每个句子都包含一个以强烈动词开头的号召性用语。">;</strong>;</p>; <p style="text-align : center; font-size: 12px;">;<a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing/calls-to-action">;<em>;图片来源</em>;</a>; </p>; <p>;如果 CTA 文案中不包含动词，您就不会提示读者采取行动，这可能会损害 CTA 的点击率并对转化产生负面影响。</p>; <h3>; 2.包括数字。</h3>; <p>;互联网上充斥着猜测和模糊的陈述。这就是为什么使用数据和数字是证明您的信息清晰明了的好方法。</p>; <p>;数字是打破歧义、具体说明您的报价并设定正确期望的好方法。数字可以准确地告诉访问者他们将获得什么、获得多少、持续多长时间等。</p>; <p>;这种技术已成功应用于号召性用语文案和博客文章标题、新闻稿标题以及电子邮件主题行。</p>; <p>;一个<a href="https://medium.com/m-meister/se-721-hugely-popular-articles-will-teach-you-a-thing-or -two-about-writing-success-1a2d863fdcc6">;研究</a>;分析了 Medium 上最受欢迎的 721 篇文章，发现第二受欢迎的起始词是数字。</p>; <p>;你能找到什么数字包含在您的 CTA 文案中吗？您可以添加您提供的白皮书的页长，提及特定的折扣，或列出您提供的特定资源的数字影响或好处。</p>; <p>;例如，HubSpot 的 CTA，用于为我们的营销请求演示产品是，“了解为什么超过 177,000 名客户使用 HubSpot 使营销规模更加人性化。”</p>; <p>;该数字强调了有多少人使用并信任 HubSpot 来满足其营销团队的需求。</p>; <p >;<img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/UtfrLfUHvlIsWGy4o8OLa7js1hVvnMkzYiLRJGqczkFD1Ci3qydSngJSHK7SAl_ZFdx2EKaNMyt8JtzGukpXIXpQvwgTAAXs3xCg9HOcEf_3lT0lfer0LhWG0hJU tO7aiEC8zGilt7_y318SmcSyfk0" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; 显示: 块; 宽度: 650px; 高度: auto; 最大宽度: 100 %;” title="" alt="如何编写号召性用语：在 CTA 中使用数字，就像 HubSpot 营销 CTA 所做的那样。">;</p>; <h3>;3. Use adverbs sparingly.</h3>; <p>;Most adverbs are recognizable by their “-ly” ending, eg, “finally,” “unfortunately,” and “quietly.”</p>; <p>;However, there are different types of adverbs (concerning direction, time, degree, and manner), and their function is to modify<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/search?index=books&amp;linkCode=qs&amp;keywords=0521276594">; “constituents other than nouns</a>;.”</p>; <p>;They have no fixed position in a sentence. For instance, you can place the word “finally” at the sentence's beginning, middle, or end.</p>; <p>;Words like “really” or “incredibly” are often considered fluff and don't add much value when a more powerful adverb could be in its place. For instance, “really hard” could replace “challenging.”</p>; <p>;Limit the number of adverbs in your CTAs unless they add value to the sentence. The first word in this CTA on Zoom's website is “securely,” which is a robust descriptor for its product.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/4-Td0Xz4aaBU4VmGGh57YdtiZfdDCnfx2nX4nUBWMVrGWTjIfeIEvdesF8Ig4BY33QaMJ-_76n4hX0QvIGF_r00YdS9IeQuqmRgRBThj0sZUQE4xDvLXgXFoCqxYv-oONj4cWVEQ6OdidwCRVeOxjnY" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" title="" alt="How to write a call to action: Zoom uses a powerful adverb in its CTA.">;</p>; <h3>;4. Keep the character count low.</h3>; <p>;The standard advice for CTAs has been to keep them concise. Don't write convoluted copy that will take your visitor long to read. (This also holds for other marketing activities, such as emails and press releases.)</p>; <p>;In an analysis of high-converting CTA buttons, <a href="https://adevolver.com/call-to-action-buttons/">;the study</a>; found that the average CTA included 3.411 words.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/eGMvfwVB4qm437r7YshCZhuC32p8Oh1eQxXLwnjMlROrJa-LMlJUm2AqRsB6RCH8psB_zgXx7diipF78wlEb_aKfZ5YEKQh7QVugDE4pqckrafyhDjzkRqGQCpFmqQLrIJgHQ1pkcH9STSH6Bb2mqX0" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" title="" alt="How to write a call to action: A bar chart that shows the average number of words used in CTA buttons is about three.">;</p>; <p>;If you want to learn how to write a CTA that captures readers' attention and gets to the point quickly, take a cue from how PR professionals write press release headlines.</p>; <p>;<a href="https://www.cision.com/resources/articles/10-takeaways-from-cision-s-state-of-the-press-release/">;Cision's State of Press Releases Report</a>; found an average headline length of 88 characters.</p>; <p>;Try to fit your CTA copy within these limits (or get some <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/campaign-assistant">;writing assistance</a>; to help craft concise messaging faster), and see how readers react. This also leads to the next point.</p>; <h3>;5. Tailor your calls-to-action to the device.</h3>; <p>;You should optimize everything from your website to the CTAs on your landing pages and emails for desktop and mobile users. This is especially true when <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/277125/share-of-website-traffic-coming-from-mobile-devices/">;mobile devices account for half of all web traffic</a>; worldwide.</p>; <p>;If your users or audience primarily use their mobile devices to search for products or read their emails, optimize your CTA copy for a smaller screen.</p>; <p>;A recent HubSpot survey of over 1,000 marketers found that <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/website/mobile-experience">;33% use mobile-friendly website design</a>; in their marketing strategy.</p>; <p>;This shows that mobile users must be prioritized when assembling everything from your website to landing pages to CTA copy.</p>; <p>;Put all of these CTA best practices into action to write more precise and concise prompts. Cut the fluff and use powerful action verbs at the beginning of your CTA so that mobile readers see the most important element first.</p>; <p>;Also, consider writing shorter CTAs that won't be at risk of getting cut off by limited screen space.</p>; <h3>;6. Make language less technical and more practical.</h3>; <p>;The language in your CTA will reflect industry-specific knowledge. However, some best practices hold for all CTA copies regardless of industry.</p>; <p>;As with the other points we've examined, this one borrows from the best practices of different marketing activities.</p>; <p>;Regarding headlines, words like “why” or “best” suggest the content can improve the reader. The same logic can apply to crafting CTA copy. Emphasize the offer's benefits and how it can make your prospects smarter.</p>; <p>;In this CTA for the task management app <a href="https://todoist.com/home">;Todoist</a>;, the headline is a simple sentence that expresses the reader's desire to become more organized.</p>; <p>;It strays away from using more complex words or phrases and offers a simple CTA of “Open Todoist.”</p>; <p>;<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/sbX9BWJKCFBlbAi-YmEk7XSQr2vjbSJ-PKD8TBd_c_ymTxr-fJVsPoWrHCuoFDDKqZbD3dHlkLPpz8A-4Vx9Hczugpgl2uyCRZDjR-gcUb-Ow0KJZ3hg3V8ElZPMtHMot31Y813RRfri-EVamIeV49Q" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" title="" alt="How to write a call to action: The CTA on the Todoist homepage reads, “Organize your work and life, finally.” The simple CTA button underneath reads, “Open Todoist.”">;</p>; <p>;When writing your CTAs, stay away from overly technical jargon. Some of the words that attract the fewest views in blog posts include “franchise,” “investment,” “virtualization,” and “conferencing.”</p>; <p>;These terms imply forced complexity and are less appealing to readers. If people don't want to <em>;view</em>; content with such technical jargon, you should not include it in your CTA copy.</p>; <h3>;7. Get creative and use personality.</h3>; <p>;CTAs don't have to be boring. You can craft a concise and compelling message by showcasing your brand's personality or speaking in your audience's language.</p>; <p>;Take the CTA example below from the email brand <a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/">;Really Good Emails</a>;. Really Good Emails curates email marketing and design examples from around the web.</p>; <p>;The brand shared a curated set of astrology-themed emails in a recent newsletter. The newsletter copy and the CTA aligned with the theme, which helped take their message even further.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/2QAa7cV4pNUQIZDKv2jZ7tQBHIGQxlXpqhXf1FmMRM-BP_CsnpdukRAZN6djYswqgE1IZUhjdJWusfdXE3mSPPfw0rvr40hQunW9WqXtK6fgXrZyf6WW0ixNowF5Kkqn7KtspyyEG05sX8mpNn9EWsA" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" title="" alt="How to write a call to action: Really Good Emails uses a themed CTA button that says “See The Stars Align” to match the rest of its astrology-themed email.">;</p>; <h2>;Writing Excellent CTAs</h2>; <p>;Writing a call-to-action is excellent practice for crafting a clear and concise message.</p>; <p>;If you want to drive more traffic, increase click-through rates, and convert more users, then knowing how to write a call-to-action is a skill all marketers must master.</p>; <div>; <div>; <a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=6185e702-0cbb-4f65-84e0-ffc0f9b39f42&amp;pid=53&amp;ecid=&amp;hseid=&amp;hsic=">;<img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; " alt="New Call to action" height="226" width="646" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/6185e702-0cbb-4f65-84e0-ffc0f9b39f42.png">;</a>; </div>; <div>; &nbsp; </div>; </div>; <img src="https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=53&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.hubspot.com%2Fblog%2Ftabid%2F6307%2Fbid%2F31435%2Fhow-to-write-call-to-action-copy-that-gets-visitors-clicking.aspx&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.hubspot.com%252Fmarketing&amp;bvt=rss" alt="" width="1" height="1" style="min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; ">; Landing Page Copy Free Landing Page Builder Wed, 25 Oct 2023 11:00:00 GMT https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/31435/how-to-write-call-to-action-copy-that-gets-visitors-clicking.aspx 2023-10-25T11:00:00Z Sam Lauron
